---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Evidence & Safety • Historical Translation Project™" description="Reputable sources, conservative claims, and safety-first disclosure.">
  <section class="container-xl section">
    <div class="kicker">Evidence & Safety</div>
    <h1 class="h2 mt-2">Reputable sources. Conservative language.</h1>
    <p class="sub mt-3">
      We build consumer dossiers using structure/function framing and reputable modern references (e.g., NIH ODS, NCCIH, WHO monographs, EMA/HMPC, PubMed-indexed reviews).
      Safety and interaction cautions are disclosed prominently.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="card-solid soft-shadow p-6">
        <div class="font-serif text-xl text-navy">Source standards</div>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          We prioritize authoritative and peer‑reviewed sources; we avoid low‑quality blogs and hype marketing.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-solid soft-shadow p-6">
        <div class="font-serif text-xl text-navy">Claim standards</div>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          We use structure/function language only (e.g., “supports digestive comfort”) and avoid disease treatment claims.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card-solid soft-shadow p-6">
        <div class="font-serif text-xl text-navy">Safety standards</div>
        <p class="text-muted mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Interactions and contraindications are highlighted. If you take medications or are pregnant/nursing, consult a clinician.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 card soft-shadow p-7">
      <div class="kicker">FDA Disclaimer</div>
      <p class="text-muted mt-2 leading-relaxed">
        These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
